channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: What we know about the pagers that exploded in Lebanon and Syria
item.description: Thousands of people were injured across Lebanon and Syria on Tuesday by an Israeli covert operation that remotely detonated pagers, ABC News sources confirmed.

item.title: Firefighter arrested at worked, charged in connection to Ohio shooting
Dockworkers at key U.S. ports threatening strike consumers could feel
item.description: About 45,000 dockworkers along the U.S. East and Gulf Coasts are threatening to strike on Oct. 1, a move that would shut down ports that handle about half the nation's cargo from ships.

item.title: China announces sanctions on US companies selling arms to self-ruled Taiwan
item.description: China has announced sanctions on American companies selling arms to the self-ruled island of Taiwan, which Beijing claims as its own territory and threatens to annex by force

item.title: Gold is having a moment — but silver is poised for its own: Morning Brief
Grand prize winner catches 20 Burmese pythons in Florida challenge
item.description: Ronald Kiger, who caught 20 Burmese pythons, won $10,000. Donna Kalil got a $2,500 prize for catching 19 snakes.

item.title: Paul Whelan thanks lawmakers for bringing him home during Capitol Hill visit
item.description: Freed American Paul Whelan, who just completed a government resettlement program in Texas following his return from wrongful detainment in Russia, thanked the lawmakers.

item.title: Scientific American makes presidential endorsement for only the second time in its 179-year history
Kansas cult accused of forcing kids to work 16-hour days without pay
item.description: Prosecutors said the group, which was labeled a cult by a federal judge in 2018, beat children and imposed severe dietary restrictions.

item.title: Google wins legal bid to overturn 1.5 billion euro antitrust fine in digital ad case
item.description: Google has won a court challenge against a 1.49 billion euro European Union antitrust fine imposed five years ago that targeted its online advertising business

item.title: George Clooney Makes Donald Trump An Offer In Taunting Clapback: ‘I Will If He Does’
Anna Sorokin appears on "Dancing With the Stars" with glittery ankle monitor
item.description: Anna Sorokin, the convicted con artist and "fake heiress," has hit the dancefloor on "Dancing With the Stars" wearing a featherweight - and very sparkly - ankle monitor.

item.title: Federal Reserve expected to cut interest rates for first time since 2020
item.description: "The time has come for policy to adjust," Fed Chair Jerome Powell said last month.

item.title: China chip stocks surge on government equipment list
Tupperware files for bankruptcy amid slumping sales
item.description: Tupperware and some of its subsidiaries have filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection, the once-iconic food container maker said in a statement.
